cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ITU and Infrastructure / Power Grid: A Single-Axiom View of K-Capital, Smart Grid, Resilience, and the 2026-2050 Infrastructure Roadmap"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209; current version
  v2.0.0 at 10.5281/zenodo.20133709) to infrastructure and power grid
  systems. Infrastructure is reframed as K_infrastructure =
  K_capital × K_network × K_maintenance — the K-skeleton (physical
  foundation) of civilization. This is Tier 1 paper #15, opening the
  K-skeleton axis and bringing the ITU polytope to 15 vertices. The
  Infrastructure vertex connects to 7 other vertices (degree 7).
  Pass-1 progress: 102 of 220 phases (46.4% — past mid-point of
  Pass-1).
  Phase 99 establishes the ITU foundation. Global infrastructure
  capital stock = $340 trillion (3.2× world GDP), annual renewal
  $10T (3% of stock). Power consumption 1990 11,800 → 2050 70,000
  TWh (5.9×). Grid inertia H = 6.0s (1990) → 1.5s (2050 NZE) — below
  the 2.5s safety threshold, requiring grid-forming batteries.
  USA ASCE 2021 grade D+ (avg score 1.49), 10-year need $3.1T
  ($1T roads alone). K_capital dynamics: 1.5% USA investment →
  29% decline over 50 years vs 2.5% sustainable.
  Phase 100 covers smart grid + AI + resilience (MILESTONE 100).
  Smart meters: 2B (2024, 20%) → 10B (2050, 95%). DERMS (rooftop
  solar + V2G + home batteries + heat pumps + smart buildings):
  480 GW (2024) → 8,500 GW (2050) — exceeding central generation
  7,000 GW (1.21× ratio). AI predictive maintenance: accuracy 90%
  (2024 advanced) → 99% (2035 AGI), cost reduction 50%, downtime
  reduction 94%. Resilience simulation under 30-day attack: AI-
  resilient grid R = 1.10 (attacks become learning opportunities)
  vs old grid R = 0.66.
  Phase 101 analyzes industry, policy, and international comparison.
  China leads with $1.5T/yr investment (8% GDP, 2.5× USA) via 新基建
  $1.4T (5yr). USA IIJA $1.2T over 10yr + IRA $369B. EU NextGenEU
  €750B + RePowerEU €300B. Japan 国土強靭化 (5yr) $100B focuses on
  aging + disaster. India NIP $1.3T. PPP global market: $20B (2000)
  → $200B (2024) → $600B (2050), 1,200 projects. Climate adaptation
  per IPCC AR6: $4.5T cumulative by 2050 (sea-level $1T, flood
  $0.8T, drought $0.7T, agriculture $0.6T, heat waves $0.5T). Major
  city projects: Singapore $100B coastal defense (2100), Tokyo $30B
  super levee + basin (2030), NY $20B The Big U (2050), Netherlands
  $15B Delta Works expansion (2050), Venice $7B MOSE (2024 complete),
  Jakarta $40B Nusantara (2045).
  Phase 102 synthesises the 2026-2050 roadmap with 19 milestones
  and 10 falsifiable predictions (P_avg = 0.55). The ITU 15-vertex
  polytope completes with K-skeleton axis. Infrastructure
  bidirectionally connects to AI/ASI (#2), Semi (#4), Economics
  (#8), Energy (#10), Climate (#11), Robotics (#13), Communications
  (#14). Communications (#14) and Climate (#11) remain tied as
  super-hubs at degree 10.
  Central thesis: infrastructure = K-skeleton (physical foundation)
  on which all other K-flows operate. dK_cap/dt = K_invest - K_decay
  is the governing equation, with most countries underfunding leading
  to intergenerational debt. AI + Robotics + Communications enable
  smart, self-healing, predictive infrastructure. Pass-1 interpretive
  paper reframing ASCE Report Card 2021, IEEE Power & Energy Society,
  IIJA/IRA/NextGenEU/Xinjianjie/国土強靭化, IPCC AR6, McKinsey,
  World Bank, IEA, Singapore Virtual Singapore, NVIDIA Omniverse in
  ITU language. Pass-2 work would derive ITU-specific K_capital
  optimization, resilience metrics, and quantitative GDP multiplier
  predictions.
